f=Executive Office/echo/marketplace/investor-update-generator/SKILL.md · tx=<!-- Unmodified copy "investor-update-generator" skill, selected fulfill catalog's "investor-update-best-practices" slot validates draft update against rubric what makes updates work, which matches "industry norms cadence, metrics selection, ask formulation" precisely many investor-update *writer* skills found during research (those write updates directly, which closer future custom investor-update-template skill, best-practices/norms slot). four files (SKILL.md scripts/ assets/ references/) copied full project workflow. --> · h2:Investor Update Generator=Validate draft monthly investor update against rubric what makes them work provide starting template you don't one yet. · h3:Clarify First=Before generating update, confirm inputs. any unknown vague, ASK assume: · h3:Clarify First=**Stage cadence** early-stage monthly later-stage quarterly changes which sections rubric expects, **This period's metrics** defined set month; re-defining metrics signals dishonest reporting, **Specific asks** what you need investors (intros, hires, advice); highest-leverage section, **Bad news risks** strong updates lead these, they surfaced, buried · h3:Clarify First=Stop rule: ask 2-3 change output. user says "just draft it," proceed list your assumptions top artifact. · h4:Workflow Monthly Update Production=First month: pull metrics dashboard, last update, current asks Draft against `assets/investor_update_template.md` Validate: `python scripts/investor_update_validator.py update.md` Send within business days month-end **Time Estimate:** 1-2 hours/month. · h4:Workflow Update Cadence Establishment=Read `references/what_makes_good_updates.md` Decide cadence: monthly standard early-stage; quarterly later-stage Pick distribution: investors only, extended (advisors, helpful operators) Commit publicly once you start, don't skip months **Time Estimate:** week set up; recurring monthly thereafter. · h3:Reference Guides=**`references/what_makes_good_updates.md`** What separates good investor updates bad · h3:Best Practices=**Send bad news first.** Investors notice they hear good., **Asks specific.** "Help sales" vague; "Intros VPs Engineering SaaS companies 100-1000 employees NA" actionable., **Cadence perfection.** consistent update beats perfect annual one., **Same metrics month.** Defining re-defining metrics signals dishonest reporting., **One page (or one screen).** Past two screens, attention drops.